Name: Victini
PkdxEntry: It creates an unlimited supply of energy inside its body, which it shares with those who touch it.

Name: Snivy
PkdxEntry: It is very intelligent and calm. Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes its movements swifter.

Name: Servine
PkdxEntry: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.

Name: Serperior
PkdxEntry: It can stop its opponents’ movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.

Name: Tepig
PkdxEntry: It can deftly dodge its foe’s attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.

Name: Pignite
PkdxEntry: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

Name: Emboar
PkdxEntry: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.

Name: Oshawott
PkdxEntry: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

Name: Dewott
PkdxEntry: Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.

Name: Samurott
PkdxEntry: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.

Name: Patrat
PkdxEntry: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.

Name: Watchog
PkdxEntry: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

Name: Lillipup
PkdxEntry: It faces strong opponents with great courage. But, when at a disadvantage in a fight, this intelligent Pokémon flees.

Name: Herdier
PkdxEntry: It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.

Name: Stoutland
PkdxEntry: It rescues people stranded by blizzards in the mountains. Its shaggy fur shields it from the cold.

Name: Purrloin
PkdxEntry: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can’t help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

Name: Liepard
PkdxEntry: These Pokémon vanish and appear unexpectedly. Many Trainers are drawn to their beautiful form and fur.

Name: Pansage
PkdxEntry: This Pokémon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.

Name: Simisage
PkdxEntry: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

Name: Pansear
PkdxEntry: When it is angered, the temperature of its head tuft reaches 600° F. It uses its tuft to roast berries.

Name: Simisear
PkdxEntry: It loves sweets because they become energy for the fire burning inside its body.

Name: Panpour
PkdxEntry: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

Name: Simipour
PkdxEntry: The tuft on its head holds water. When the level runs low, it replenishes the tuft by siphoning up water with its tail.

Name: Munna
PkdxEntry: Munna always float in the air. People whose dreams are eaten by them forget what the dreams had been about.

Name: Musharna
PkdxEntry: The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokémon.

Name: Pidove
PkdxEntry: Each follows its Trainer’s orders as best it can, but they sometimes fail to understand complicated commands.

Name: Tranquill
PkdxEntry: It can return to its Trainer’s location regardless of the distance separating them.

Name: Unfezant
PkdxEntry: Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females’ flying abilities surpass those of the males.

Name: Blitzle
PkdxEntry: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use their flashing manes to communicate with one another.

Name: Zebstrika
PkdxEntry: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

Name: Roggenrola
PkdxEntry: Its ear is hexagonal in shape. Compressed underground, its body is as hard as steel.

Name: Boldore
PkdxEntry: When it overflows with power, the orange crystal on its body glows. It looks for underground water in caves.

Name: Gigalith
PkdxEntry: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.

Name: Woobat
PkdxEntry: Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.

Name: Swoobat
PkdxEntry: It emits sound waves of various frequencies from its nose, including some powerful enough to destroy rocks.

Name: Drilbur
PkdxEntry: It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.

Name: Excadrill
PkdxEntry: It can help in tunnel construction. Its drill has evolved into steel strong enough to bore through iron plates.

Name: Audino
PkdxEntry: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

Name: Timburr
PkdxEntry: It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle the lumber without difficulty.

Name: Gurdurr
PkdxEntry: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

Name: Conkeldurr
PkdxEntry: They use concrete pillars as walking canes. They know moves that enable them to swing the pillars freely in battle.

Name: Tympole
PkdxEntry: They warn others of danger by vibrating their cheeks to create a high-pitched sound.

Name: Palpitoad
PkdxEntry: When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, they can make waves in water or earthquake-like vibrations on land.

Name: Seismitoad
PkdxEntry: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.

Name: Throh
PkdxEntry: When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. Wild Throh use vines to weave their own belts.

Name: Sawk
PkdxEntry: The sound of Sawk punching boulders and trees can be heard all the way from the mountains where they train.

Name: Sewaddle
PkdxEntry: This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.

Name: Swadloon
PkdxEntry: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

Name: Leavanny
PkdxEntry: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using the cutters on its arms and sticky silk.

Name: Venipede
PkdxEntry: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.

Name: Whirlipede
PkdxEntry: Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.

Name: Scolipede
PkdxEntry: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

Name: Cottonee
PkdxEntry: When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton from its body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distract the attacker.

Name: Whimsicott
PkdxEntry: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

Name: Petilil
PkdxEntry: The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating one of these leaves is known to refresh a tired body.

Name: Lilligant
PkdxEntry: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities.

Name: Basculin
PkdxEntry: Red and blue Basculin get along so poorly, they’ll start fighting instantly. These Pokémon are very hostile.

Name: Sandile
PkdxEntry: They live buried in the sands of the desert. The sun-warmed sands prevent their body temperature from dropping.

Name: Krokorok
PkdxEntry: They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms.

Name: Krookodile
PkdxEntry: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.

Name: Darumaka
PkdxEntry: When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.

Name: Darmanitan
PkdxEntry: Its internal fire burns at 2,500° F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.

Name: Maractus
PkdxEntry: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokémon that prey on its flower seeds.

Name: Dwebble
PkdxEntry: This Pokémon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.

Name: Crustle
PkdxEntry: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

Name: Scraggy
PkdxEntry: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.

Name: Scrafty
PkdxEntry: Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.

Name: Sigilyph
PkdxEntry: They never vary the route they fly, because their memories of guarding an ancient city remain steadfast.

Name: Yamask
PkdxEntry: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.

Name: Cofagrigus
PkdxEntry: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.

Name: Tirtouga
PkdxEntry: Restored from a fossil, this Pokémon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.

Name: Carracosta
PkdxEntry: They can live both in the ocean and on land. A slap from one of them is enough to open a hole in the bottom of a tanker.

Name: Archen
PkdxEntry: Revived from a fossil, this Pokémon is thought to be the ancestor of all bird Pokémon.

Name: Archeops
PkdxEntry: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.

Name: Trubbish
PkdxEntry: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

Name: Garbodor
PkdxEntry: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.

Name: Zorua
PkdxEntry: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.

Name: Zoroark
PkdxEntry: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.

Name: Minccino
PkdxEntry: They greet one another by rubbing each other with their tails, which are always kept well groomed and clean.

Name: Cinccino
PkdxEntry: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.

Name: Gothita
PkdxEntry: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.

Name: Gothorita
PkdxEntry: Starlight is the source of their power. At night, they mark star positions by using psychic power to float stones.

Name: Gothitelle
PkdxEntry: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.

Name: Solosis
PkdxEntry: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

Name: Duosion
PkdxEntry: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.

Name: Reuniclus
PkdxEntry: These remarkably intelligent Pokémon fight by controlling arms that can grip with rock-crushing power.

Name: Ducklett
PkdxEntry: These bird Pokémon are excellent divers. They swim around in the water eating their favorite food--peat moss.

Name: Swanna
PkdxEntry: It administers sharp, powerful pecks with its bill. It whips its long neck to deliver forceful repeated strikes.

Name: Vanillite
PkdxEntry: The temperature of their breath is -58° F. They create snow crystals and make snow fall in the areas around them.

Name: Vanillish
PkdxEntry: Snowy mountains are this Pokémon’s habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.

Name: Vanilluxe
PkdxEntry: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and attack their foes with violent blizzards.

Name: Deerling
PkdxEntry: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.

Name: Deerling
PkdxEntry: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.

Name: Deerling
PkdxEntry: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.

Name: Deerling
PkdxEntry: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.

Name: Sawsbuck
PkdxEntry: The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.

Name: Sawsbuck
PkdxEntry: The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.

Name: Sawsbuck
PkdxEntry: The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.

Name: Sawsbuck
PkdxEntry: The plants growing on its horns change according to the season. The leaders of the herd possess magnificent horns.

Name: Emolga
PkdxEntry: The energy made in its cheeks’ electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.

Name: Karrablast
PkdxEntry: These mysterious Pokémon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.

Name: Escavalier
PkdxEntry: They fly around at high speed, striking with their pointed spears. Even when in trouble, they face opponents bravely.

Name: Foongus
PkdxEntry: It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poké Ball is unknown.

Name: Amoonguss
PkdxEntry: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.

Name: Frillish
PkdxEntry: With its thin, veil-like arms wrapped around the body of its opponent, it sinks to the ocean floor.

Name: Jellicent
PkdxEntry: They propel themselves by expelling absorbed seawater from their bodies. Their favorite food is life energy.

Name: Alomomola
PkdxEntry: Floating in the open sea is how they live. When they find a wounded Pokémon, they embrace it and bring it to shore.

Name: Joltik
PkdxEntry: They attach themselves to large-bodied Pokémon and absorb static electricity, which they store in an electric pouch.

Name: Galvantula
PkdxEntry: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.

Name: Ferroseed
PkdxEntry: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.

Name: Ferrothorn
PkdxEntry: It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. A hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.

Name: Klink
PkdxEntry: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.

Name: Klang
PkdxEntry: By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feelings to others. When angry, it rotates faster.

Name: Klinklang
PkdxEntry: Its red core functions as an energy tank. It fires the charged energy through its spikes into an area.

Name: Tynamo
PkdxEntry: While one alone doesn’t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

Name: Eelektrik
PkdxEntry: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.

Name: Eelektross
PkdxEntry: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

Name: Elgyem
PkdxEntry: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent’s brain, causing unendurable headaches.

Name: Beheeyem
PkdxEntry: It can manipulate an opponent’s memory. Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three different-colored fingers.

Name: Litwick
PkdxEntry: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.

Name: Lampent
PkdxEntry: It arrives near the moment of death and steals spirit from the body.

Name: Chandelure
PkdxEntry: It absorbs a spirit, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.

Name: Axew
PkdxEntry: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.

Name: Fraxure
PkdxEntry: Since a broken tusk will not grow back, they diligently sharpen their tusks on river rocks after they’ve been fighting.

Name: Haxorus
PkdxEntry: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.

Name: Cubchoo
PkdxEntry: When it is not feeling well, its mucus gets watery and the power of its Ice-type moves decreases.

Name: Beartic
PkdxEntry: It can make its breath freeze at will. Very able in the water, it swims around in northern seas and catches prey.

Name: Cryogonal
PkdxEntry: When its body temperature goes up, it turns into steam and vanishes. When its temperature lowers, it returns to ice.

Name: Shelmet
PkdxEntry: When attacked, it defends itself by closing the lid of its shell. It can spit a sticky, poisonous liquid.

Name: Accelgor
PkdxEntry: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.

Name: Stunfisk
PkdxEntry: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.

Name: Mienfoo
PkdxEntry: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.

Name: Mienshao
PkdxEntry: It wields the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arm attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot even be seen.

Name: Druddigon
PkdxEntry: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.

Name: Golett
PkdxEntry: The energy that burns inside it enables it to move, but no one has yet been able to identify this energy.

Name: Golurk
PkdxEntry: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.

Name: Pawniard
PkdxEntry: Blades comprise this Pokémon’s entire body. If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.

Name: Bisharp
PkdxEntry: It leads a group of Pawniard. It battles to become the boss, but will be driven from the group if it loses.

Name: Bouffalant
PkdxEntry: They charge wildly and headbutt everything. Their headbutts have enough destructive force to derail a train.

Name: Rufflet
PkdxEntry: They crush berries with their talons. They bravely stand up to any opponent, no matter how strong it is.

Name: Braviary
PkdxEntry: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.

Name: Vullaby
PkdxEntry: Its wings are too tiny to allow it to fly. As the time approaches for it to evolve, it discards the bones it was wearing.

Name: Mandibuzz
PkdxEntry: It makes a nest out of bones it finds. It grabs weakened prey in its talons and hauls it to its nest of bones.

Name: Heatmor
PkdxEntry: It breathes through a hole in its tail while it burns with an internal fire. Durant is its prey.

Name: Durant
PkdxEntry: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.

Name: Deino
PkdxEntry: They cannot see, so they tackle and bite to learn about their surroundings. Their bodies are covered in wounds.

Name: Zweilous
PkdxEntry: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.

Name: Hydreigon
PkdxEntry: This brutal Pokémon travels the skies on its six wings. Anything that moves seems like a foe to it, triggering its attack.

Name: Larvesta
PkdxEntry: This Pokémon was believed to have been born from the sun. When it evolves, its entire body is engulfed in flames.

Name: Volcarona
PkdxEntry: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona’s fire provided a replacement for the sun.

Name: Cobalion
PkdxEntry: It has a body and heart of steel. Its glare is sufficient to make even an unruly Pokémon obey it.

Name: Terrakion
PkdxEntry: Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokémon is spoken of in legends.

Name: Virizion
PkdxEntry: Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Using whirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftly cuts opponents.

Name: Tornadus
PkdxEntry: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

Name: Thundurus
PkdxEntry: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.

Name: Reshiram
PkdxEntry: This Pokémon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.

Name: Zekrom
PkdxEntry: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

Name: Landorus
PkdxEntry: The energy that comes pouring from its tail increases the nutrition in the soil, making crops grow to great size.

Name: Kyurem
PkdxEntry: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

Name: Keldeo
PkdxEntry: It crosses the world, running over the surfaces of oceans and rivers. It appears at scenic waterfronts.

Name: Meloetta
PkdxEntry: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

Name: Genesect
PkdxEntry: Over 300 million years ago, it was feared as the strongest of hunters. It has been modified by Team Plasma.
